The 13th Provincial Tea Exposition opens - Viewpoint Headlines - Hunan Daily Network - Huasheng Online
Hunan Daily December 10th News (All-Media Reporter Zhang Shangwu, Hu Panpan, Correspondent Liu Xiaoling, Photography Li Jian) This morning, the 13th Hunan Tea Industry Exposition and New Tea Promotion Conference was held at the Hunan International Convention and Exhibition Center, showcasing the tea industry, innovating tea technology, promoting tea culture, and accelerating the goal of the trillion-dollar tea industry.
Deputy Director of the National Supply and Marketing Cooperative Society of the Chinese Federation, Hou Shunli, and Vice Chairman of the Standing Committee of the Provincial People's Congress, Ye Hongzhan, attended the opening ceremony.
Professor Liu Zhonghua, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, launched the opening ceremony: The source of Lake Red is in Xinhua, and the rise of black tea injects new energy into "Five-Colored Hunan Tea.
"In recent years, the provincial government and government have strongly supported the development of the tea industry, promoted the construction of the trillion-dollar Hunan tea industry, and formed the development pattern of "Three Hunans, Four Waters, Five Colors Tea."
The tea industry in the province is increasing innovation, with main tea categories such as green tea, black tea, and red tea taking turns to lead, and the main tea producing areas promoting the integration of tea and tourism, driving increased income for tea farmers.
The tide turns, and red tea is once again gaining strength.
Tea industry experts in the province say that by picking green tea first, then red tea, and black tea, tea farmers have income all year round and the value of tea gardens is steadily increasing.
At the opening ceremony, the provincial leaders awarded certificates to the fourth batch of enterprises authorized to use the "Hunan Red Tea" trademark, and Xinya welcomed the "Source of Hunan Red".
At the Xinya Red Tea Pavilion, a Fujian tea merchant was impressed by a high mountain tea called "Bingli Chun" and immediately placed an order.
The Secretary General of the Provincial Tea Association, Wang Zhun, happily said that the current epidemic and other factors more or less affect the tea market, but from the tea expo, highlights are everywhere.
The Newhua Red Tea brings a touch of red, infused with the cultural connotations of tea, and its popularity and transaction are hot, bringing a new spring to the tea industry in Hunan.